## 3. User Personas & Flows

### 3.1 User Personas

#### 1. EV Fleet Admin
- **Goal:** Enterprise-wide fleet governance and strategy
- **Key Actions:** Monitor global KPIs, approve contracts, track penalties, review RD investigations
- **Primary Dashboard:** Global KPI view, contract analytics, penalty forecasting

#### 2. Depot Manager
- **Goal:** Maximize local fleet uptime and KPI adherence
- **Key Actions:** Plan duties, assign buses/drivers, manage breakdowns, schedule maintenance, track daily reports
- **Primary Dashboard:** Depot ops, live fleet monitor, shift planning, daily closeout

#### 3. Driver
- **Goal:** Execute trips safely and efficiently
- **Key Actions:** View duty, start/end trips, receive behavior feedback, log incidents
- **Primary Touchpoint:** Mobile app (RFID attendance, trip tracking, behavior scoring)

#### 4. RSA / Support Team
- **Goal:** Resolve breakdowns and support operations
- **Key Actions:** Triage tickets, dispatch roadside assistance, coordinate spare bus allocation
- **Primary Dashboard:** Ticket queue, priority alerts, SLA tracking

#### 5. RD / Product Development
- **Goal:** Drive vehicle quality and innovation
- **Key Actions:** Analyze vehicle performance trends, fault patterns, battery aging, test new features
- **Primary Dashboard:** Vehicle Performance Console, Digital Twin, fault analysis

#### 6. Manufacturing / Service
- **Goal:** Quality assurance and field service management
- **Key Actions:** Device–VIN mapping, EOL/PDI testing, warranty claim investigation, firmware OTA
- **Primary Interface:** Manufacturing & Service Console

#### 7. Retail Fleet Operator
- **Goal:** Monitor owned buses, manage warranty, schedule maintenance
- **Key Actions:** View vehicle status, warranty coverage, upcoming services, raise claims
- **Primary Portal:** Retail Fleet Operator Portal (read-only, scoped to own VINs)

### 3.2 Core User Flows

#### Flow 1: Depot Manager Daily Operations
```
Login → Depot Dashboard
  ├─ View KPIs (uptime, penalties, fleet status)
  ├─ Plan Duties (assign routes, buses, drivers)
  ├─ Monitor Live Fleet (map, SOC, alerts)
  │  ├─ On breakdown → Create RSA ticket, allocate spare
  │  ├─ On low SOC → Adjust charging schedule
  │  └─ On driver violation → Flag for coaching
  ├─ Schedule Maintenance (mark downtime)
  └─ Close-of-day Report (export, summary, notes)
```

#### Flow 2: Retail Fleet Operator After-Sales
```
Login → Retail Home (OWN vehicles only)
  ├─ View Fleet Cards (warranty status, upcoming services)
  ├─ Click Bus → Bus Detail
  │  ├─ Warranty & Alerts tab
  │  │  ├─ View warranty status (in/near expiry/out)
  │  │  └─ Raise Warranty Claim (pre-filled with GOCC data)
  │  ├─ Maintenance tab
  │  │  ├─ View upcoming services
  │  │  └─ Book/Reschedule service (confirm slot)
  │  └─ Alerts & Status (basic health)
  └─ Reports (warranty coverage, service schedule, fault history)
```

#### Flow 3: Alert Generation & Escalation
```
Telematics Device → Kafka Stream
  → Flink CEP (rule evaluation)
    ├─ Low SOC (< 15%) → Immediate alert to Depot Manager
    ├─ High batt temp (> 50°C) → Critical alert to RSA
    ├─ Fault code (e.g., BMS error) → Log to RD, alert ops
    ├─ Overspeed / Harsh brake → Driver behavior event + score
    └─ Non-communication (> 30 min) → Device health alert
  → Store in TimescaleDB + Elasticsearch
  → Push to GOCC dashboard + alert channels
```

