## 9. Security & Compliance

### 9.1 Security Measures

| Layer | Control | Implementation |
|---|---|---|
| **Transport** | TLS 1.3 | All HTTPS/WSS, ALB enforces 443 only |
| **Authentication** | JWT + OAuth2 | OpenID Connect, Keycloak, MFA optional |
| **Authorization** | RBAC + RLS | Role-based UI/API access + DB row filtering |
| **Data at rest** | Encryption | RDS encrypted (KMS), encrypted columns for IMEI/SIM (pgcrypto) |
| **Input validation** | Parameterized queries | Prevent SQL injection, input sanitization |
| **Rate limiting** | Token bucket | 100 req/15min per org, 10 transfers/hour per org |
| **Audit logging** | CloudWatch + S3 | All sensitive actions logged with user, org, timestamp |
| **Secrets management** | AWS Secrets Manager | Encrypted storage, rotation, least privilege |

### 9.2 OWASP Top 10 Compliance

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| A01: Broken Access Control | RLS policies + RBAC checks on every endpoint |
| A02: Cryptographic Failures | TLS 1.3, AES-256 encryption at rest, pgcrypto for PII |
| A03: Injection | Parameterized queries, input validation (express-validator) |
| A04: Insecure Design | Threat modeling, security by design, separation of concerns |
| A05: Security Misconfiguration | Terraform hardening, security groups, WAF rules |
| A06: Vulnerable Dependencies | npm audit, Snyk scanning, automated patch management |
| A07: Identification Failures | JWT tokens, optional MFA, secure session management |
| A08: Data Integrity | Signed transfers, audit trails, transaction rollback |
| A09: Logging & Monitoring | CloudWatch, ELK, alerting, incident response procedures |
| A10: SSRF | Network isolation, VPC, private RDS, no public endpoints |

