## 10. Performance & Scalability

### 10.1 Performance Targets

| Metric | Target | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| **API latency (p95)** | < 200ms | Connection pooling, DB indexing, Redis caching |
| **Telemetry ingest rate** | 50K msg/sec | Kafka brokers, stream processing, partitioning |
| **Telematics query latency** | < 100ms for last N records | TimescaleDB partitions, hypertables, compression |
| **Dashboard load time** | < 2s | Materialized views, pre-aggregated KPIs, CDN for static assets |
| **Concurrent users** | 5K+ | Auto-scaling ECS, RDS connection pooling, Redis cache |

### 10.2 Optimization Strategies

- **Caching:** Redis for session, KPI aggregates, frequently accessed lookups
- **Pagination:** All list endpoints return max 100 rows, offset-based or cursor-based
- **Indexing:** Composite indices on commonly filtered columns (org_id, vehicle_id, ts_utc)
- **Materialized Views:** Pre-computed dashboards refreshed hourly or on-demand
- **Query optimization:** EXPLAIN ANALYZE, avoid N+1 queries (JOINs, batch queries)
- **Compression:** TimescaleDB compression for telemetry older than 7 days
- **Partitioning:** By org_id, vehicle_id, time (daily for telemetry)

